When importing sub-tasks in a CSV file, if the parent issue already exists in JIRA and has a Fix Version set, and in the import process the FixVersion field is not mapped, the field is overwritten. 
In our documentation regarding [CSV import|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Importing+Data+from+CSV] we state: 
{quote}Importing a CSV to update existing issues will reset columns to their default values if they are not specified in the CSV.{quote}

However, this seems to be true only to the Fix Version field. If we import issues in the same condition and the Assignee field is not mapped, it is not overwritten.

